RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMILES FOR DAVID had the lead after the break, was reined back to track the frontrunner on the rail by the half, rallied inside splitting runners in the two path turning for home and tenaciously battled to the wire winning the bob at the finish line. GENTLE SEAS settled four deep in the middle of the pack down the backstretch, advanced smartly outside foes at the half, tracked the leader three wide around the turn, pounced three wide outside straightening out for the drive, poked her head in front at the eighth pole and gamely fought to the wire losing the photo at the finish. LOOK AT LIL SISTER was hustled at the start outside to take command by the half mile marker, set the fractions on the fence around the bend, was collared outside at the quarter pole, was no match for the top two in the stretch but held for a clear third in the end. JIMMY IS A BREEZE stalked near the rear in the early stages, began to pick up rivals midway through the turn, nudged for more at the quarter pole and willingly finished up down the stretch for a minor share. HARD ROCK WARRIOR had one beat down the backside, trailed entering the turn, edged closer to the pack at the quarter pole, angled outside four wide at the top of the stretch and finished with intent battling for a minor share in the end. CLASSICALCROSSOVER travelled in mid-pack on the rail with a half mile to run, crept closer on the fence running around the turn, was in range for a share at the top of the lane but needed more late to be a factor at the wire. TANGERINE TWIST was under a tight hold watching the front two at the half, chased the pacesetter on the turn, bid for the lead with horses on each side in the two path at the quarter pole, could not find another gear turning for home and faltered in upper stretch. SMART IRENE was unhurried trailing in the early going, made a brief and early move four wide around foes at the three furlong marker, could not sustain the run and had little to show in the stretch run. FEROCIOUS QUEEN prompted the pace at the start, was then relegated to settle in midfield on the rail between foes at the half, could not keep up to runners through the turn and came up empty for the stretch drive.
